#: src/index.md:1
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:3
msgid ""
"_rustup_ installs [The Rust Programming Language](https://www.rust-lang.org) "
"from the official release channels, enabling you to easily switch between "
"stable, beta, and nightly compilers and keep them updated. It makes cross-"
"compiling simpler with binary builds of the standard library for common "
"platforms. And it runs on all platforms Rust supports."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:9
msgid ""
"Check out the [Concepts](concepts/index.md) chapter for an overview of how "
"rustup works and some of the terminology it uses. The [Installation]"
"(installation/index.md) chapter covers installing rustup and getting started."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:13
msgid ""
"The source code of rustup and this manual may be found at <https://github."
"com/rust-lang/rustup>. If you find a problem, check out the [issue tracker]"
"(https://github.com/rust-lang/rustup/issues)."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:17
msgid ""
"Release notes for rustup may be found in the [CHANGELOG](https://github.com/"
"rust-lang/rustup/blob/HEAD/CHANGELOG.md)."
msgstr ""
